cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a framework for tooth morphometry using statistical shape analysis, which involves landmark-matching Teichmuller maps and quasi-conformal theory. This work involves computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) techniques for establishing a 1-1 correspondence between tooth surfaces and building a tooth classification scheme. The use of statistical shape analysis also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) methods. Finally, the dataset used in the experiment involves medical imaging (cs.MM) of human premolars.
